to contribute a few pieces to the puzzle...

I'm not sure about the build system but the root problem is I think here

   http://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=534458

where texi2dvi --pdf fails to remove the ~; texi2dvi --pdf is used by R to build 
vignettes. The release build system uses openSUSE 12.1, whereas devel has ubuntu 
12.04 and presumably different version sof texi2pdf. I can confirm the bug on my 
ubuntu 12.04 system with

$ cat > x.tex
\documentclass{article}
\begin{document}
Foo~bar.
\end{document}
/tmp$ texi2dvi --pdf x.tex


